section 22(4) of the legal practitioners act 1974 (nt) relevantly provided: a legal practitioner is not entitled to recover any costs or disbursements in respect of any work of a professional nature done by him as a legal practitioner if, at the time at which the work was done, he was not the holder of a current unrestricted practising certificate or restricted certificate class 2.
mellor j and lush j, each at 336, agreed with this view.
kent v ward (1894) 70 ltns 612 and browne v barber [1913] 2 kb 553 held to the same effect as fowler .